Looking at the response to the AMOC weakening, i.e. HOS-CTL, we see that the spatial pattern of regions that have increased or decreased exchange with the atmosphere is very similar for SSP1-2.6 as for SSP5-8.5 (Fig. 3c, f). In total, the ocean takes up 7.4 PgC less due to the AMOC weakening in SSP1-2.6 and 15.6 PgC less in SSP5-8.5 (Fig. 4a, b).Fig. 3
