				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$^2$$\end{document}2-values ranging from 0.79 to 0.97 for both emission scenarios. Especially the relations between NPP and the gas exchange are strong: 0.97 and 0.96 for SSP1-2.6 and SSP5-8.5, respectively.

