The regions with sea ice show similar behavior as the Arctic Ocean with decreased uptake related to a larger sea-ice cover in the HOS simulations (Fig. 5). In the ice-free subpolar region, an increase in uptake is observed (Fig. 5a, b). The linear regression analysis shows that the trend in gas exchange is determined by the dilution of Alk by the freshwater forcing (R\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
