In the subtropical region we generally see a decrease in uptake (Fig. 5a, b). To explain this we consider several variables, i.e. SST (Fig. 5g, h and S10), SSS (Fig. 5i, j and S11), DIC (Fig. 5k, l and S14), Alk (Fig. 5m, n and S15) and NPP (Fig. 5o, p and S9), which all show a relative decrease in this region. The net effect of the changes in these variables is a reduction in pH (Fig. 5e, f and S16) and reduced uptake capacity of the ocean. This is supported by the linear regression analysis between the decadal trends in the gas exchange and surface pH with R\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
